Your looking at a very nice custom built Ruger 10/22.



It has a 20" Butler Creek stainless steel barrel that has been reworked with a Bentz match grade chamber. Comes with a BSA platinum 6-24x44 scope. The bolt and trigger group have been completely worked. The hammer has been lightened, set screw in hammer to adjust the sear engagement, radius ground on the bottom of hammer for over travel, set screw in sear to reduce creep, set screw for adjustable trigger return pressure, over travel set screw in trigger gaurd, auto bolt release, The bolt has been chamfered, stoned and headspaced to .0425, firing pin has been staked, bolt buffer, set screws in the rear action to lock the trigger group and some misc polishing and stoning. It also has a extended bolt release and Kidd extended bolt handle.

title: For Sale:  Eltro-Zeiss Fero Z-51 Night Vision Scope
postcontent:
http://cgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewItem&item=REDACTED76

This is a Generation I scope, but is much better performing than the commonly available commercial grade models. Civilian market Generation I commercial scopes use a single Image Intensifier Tube (IIT) , amplifying the light and providing an image to the user. This scope however, was designed for military application, and uses three IIT's in a cascading layout, running the light from one tube to the next, further enhancing the image and giving a much better picture. Image quality from this scope can be compared to commercial Gen II, which usually run in the $2000 range.

The Z-51 was developed around 1976 by renowned optics maker Carl Zeiss AG, designed for use by the German Army (Bundeswehr) during the Cold War. The scope features a large objective diameter lens, adjustable magnification, flash protection from bursts of light, and a rugged build quality designed to thrive in a battlefield environment. This is an incredibly well designed scope, and has much better glass than its Soviet counterparts, like the 1PN34, giving a superior image with very little fish-eye and a clearer picture. The rubberized protective cap on the objective lens is intact, and removable. The removable eyepiece is also rubberized and attached to the scope with a steel string, and features two small shutters that open when the user looks through it, preventing light from escaping and revealing the user.

The scope is carried in an original Bundeswehr heavy-duty waterproof fiberglass case, with serial numbers and labeling stamped on each side. Inside the case are the mounts used to attach the scope to a variety of weapons, a sight adjustment tool, Allen wrenches, cleaning cloth, plastic sleeves, 4 brand new C-Cell batteries, and the 4 original batteries than came with the kit. All of the claw mounts are solid metal machined by Heckler & Koch, and still retain most of their finish, with no rust present. The carrying case has two latches, one of which is damaged, but the case still provides a strong seal against the elements.

The scope can be attached to any Picatinny rail on a firearm, but make sure you have high enough clearance for the objective lens to clear the receiver.

These arrived in the United States a few years ago and were being sold online from $750 and up per kit, and were sold out within days of arrival. This is a rare piece to find in a complete and functioning condition. This is an excellent value as both a collectors item and as a functioning, useable night vision scope.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Military issued Israeli Mossad Tanfoglio 9mm pistol / CZ75
postcontent:
I've got a very nice MOSSAD marked 9mm Tanfoglio pistol. For those who aren't familiar with these, they were made in the same valley as Beretta in Italy by Tanfoglio, but these pistols were made for the Israeli military under contract and thus have "MOSSAD" with two 6 point "Star of David" on the slide. This classic pistol is based upon the classic loved CZ-75 design. Frame says "Made by Fratelli Tanfoglio S.P.A. for "Weapons House LTD" - Israel".  Bore/barrel look good, no pitting and good distinct grooves, 9mm 16 round mag double stack. One mag included. Additional mags are plentiful as they take the same mags as current CZ75, Baby Eagle, Jericho, Springfield p9 and Tanfoglio Witness pistols - this pistol is the same basic design as all of these (CZ75 clones that are still being made today). 

This is neat opportunity to own a very uniquely marked and rich historic pistol used to defend the nation of Israel. Many believe that Israeli Mossad officers originally may used this weapon as their "home" carry protection. For those that may not know, the Israeli Mossad is roughly the equivalent of our FBI/CIA. A very rare and potentially valuable addition to many collections. 

Please email or call or text REDACTED. I can also ship FFL to FFL if out of state. $420 includes new Rose wood grip set as seen in pictures.

title: For Sale:  .303 P-14 Enfield
location: South side of the river, Greenville, North Carolina
postcontent:
For sale is a Pattern 14 Enfield rifle made by Eddystone. These rifles are externally almost identical to the M1917 "Enfield", and were produced for Britian during the First World War prior to 1917. When we entered the war the factories were retooled to .30-60, resulting in the M1917. This particular rifle has matching numbers, but is missing both arms of the long range volley sight. Unless you're firing at over 1,600 yards (1 mile) this shouldn't be an issue, it was probably done by the British Army. Bluing is worn and the stock has the usual service rifle dings, but rifle has matching numbers and is covered in British proofmarks, barrel is very clean and crisp. No import marks. Overall an excellent example of a very hard to find WWI era rifle.

Please note- I will at least run a quick search of your name, if you have any legal troubles that will prevent you from owning a firearm, I won't do business with you.

History of Rock Island Amory

Rock Island Armory, the leading M1911 manufacturer and developer, was acquired by Armscor Precision International in 1985. Armscor traces its roots back as far as 1905 to a small trading post in the Philippines but it wasn't until 1980 after the formerly Squires Bingham Manufacturing, was reorganized and renamed "Arms Corporation of the Philippines."

A third generation family company, Armscor is becoming a global force – now exporting to over 50 countries on 6 continents. Rock Island Armory is now the sole producer of Armscor firearms.

Rock Island Armory 1911

The Rock Island Amory (RIA) 1911 series consists of single-action recoil operated Semi-Automatic Pistols manufactured in the Philippines. The RIA 1911 is a clone of the US Military G.I. 1911-A1, the standard issue pistol from 1911 to 1985. With a smaller price tag, Rock Island Armory 1911s are an entry-level gun for the 1911 model; however the Tactical, Compact and Match models offer some additional high-end features like enhanced combat sights, ambidextrous safety, and target-grade hammer and trigger.
